GEOGRAPHIC AND ELEVATIONAL DISTRI- BUTIONS: The only known sample of 

Bunomys karokophilus

consists of the specimens collected along the Sungai Sadaunta (
823– 1006 m
) in the drainage of the larger Sungai Miu, and in the watershed of Danau Lindu in the vicinity of Tomado (
1000 m
) and Sungai Tokararu (
1150 m
); see gazetteer and the map in figure 50. No specimens exist in older collections stored in the world’s museums I have visited.

